data.description: Fantastic smaller acreage with approx 800' of Colorado River frontage. This stretch of the river offers a shallower sand bar area great for wading and perfect for launching kayaks along with deeper holes of water for catching the big one! Tree cover includes scattered live oaks, mesquites and elms. Brookesmith water tap available and electric crosses the property. Ag Exempt. Great deer, turkey and hog hunting in this area. Plant a food plot and fill some feeders and they will come! Perfect place to enjoy the outdoors, fish, hunt, swim and look for Indian artifacts! Owner is willing to divide into 15 acre tracts.
